parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among all requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

parameters.name: DryRun
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to perform a dry run, without performing the actual request. Valid values:

*   **true**: performs only a dry run. The system checks the request for potential issues, including missing parameter values, incorrect request syntax, and service limits. If the request fails the dry run, an error code is returned. If the request passes the dry run, the `DryRunOperation` error code is returned.
*   **false** (default): performs a dry run and performs the actual request.

parameters.name: GroupIpAddress
parameters.description: The IP address of the multicast group to which the multicast members belong.

parameters.name: NetworkInterfaceIds
parameters.description: The IDs of elastic network interfaces (ENIs).

parameters.name: PeerTransitRouterMulticastDomains
parameters.description: The ID of the multicast domain that is in a different region.

parameters.name: TransitRouterMulticastDomainId
parameters.description: The ID of the multicast domain to which the multicast members belong.
